or a money order, doesn't matter.

20:43.680 --> 20:46.035
Actually, I want it in a money order.

20:46.240 --> 20:48.879
And make it out to
"lce Station Zebra Associates."

20:49.080 --> 20:51.435
That's my loan-out. It's totally legit.

20:51.640 --> 20:53.596
It's done just for tax purposes.

20:53.800 --> 20:56.234
And after that,
we can discuss Visa or MasterCard...

20:56.440 --> 21:00.149
...but definitely not American Express,
so don't even ask. All right?

21:00.360 --> 21:01.349
Any questions?

21:04.280 --> 21:06.077
You're gonna get me off, right?

21:07.120 --> 21:10.749
What do I look like, your high-school
girlfriend? Five fingers, no waiting?

21:11.360 --> 21:14.477
That's a joke, Brandon. Lighten up.

21:15.000 --> 21:18.310
Son, I promise you this.

21:18.520 --> 21:21.512
I will give you
the best criminal defence...

21:21.720 --> 21:23.039
...that money can buy.

21:24.920 --> 21:26.956
Yeah, but, Francesca,
I took these already.

21:27.160 --> 21:28.798
Didn't I take these already?

21:29.000 --> 21:31.833
It's on your head. You're not
supposed to double up on vitamin A.

21:32.040 --> 21:33.837
It's bad for the liver.

21:35.360 --> 21:37.396
Okay, who's next?

21:37.600 --> 21:39.750
Did him. I did him.

21:39.960 --> 21:42.110
That one went public defender.
Thanks for nothing.

21:42.320 --> 21:45.278
What happened to my masturbator?
You got me all turned around.

21:45.800 --> 21:47.279
Hang on. I'll get back to you.

21:48.520 --> 21:52.035
I sense you're discussing my client.
Anything you care to share with me?

21:52.240 --> 21:54.754
Sure. Your commercials?
They suck ass.

21:55.440 --> 21:57.954
I've seen better acting
in an epileptic whorehouse.

21:58.160 --> 21:59.832
Is that like the one
your mom works at?

22:00.040 --> 22:02.713
Is she still offering
the two-for-one discount?

22:02.920 --> 22:05.673
DEA, huh? For a street bust.

22:05.880 --> 22:08.872
Now, what would two feds
want with that little twerp?

22:22.400 --> 22:24.277
Sooner or later,
this was gonna happen.

22:24.480 --> 22:26.710
You want your exponential growth...

22:26.920 --> 22:28.876
...guys are gonna get busted.
Simple as that.

22:29.080 --> 22:31.878
How about we get him a real attorney?
What the hell is this?

22:32.080 --> 22:33.672
This is who he hires?

22:33.880 --> 22:36.758
What? Are you kidding me?
This is the guy you want.

22:38.120 --> 22:39.678
This is the guy I'd hire.

22:40.440 --> 22:41.759
It's the guy you'd hire.

22:41.960 --> 22:43.234
Look, you remember Emilio?

22:43.680 --> 22:46.433
Okay, this dude got Emilio off,
like, twice. Okay?

22:46.640 --> 22:50.997
Both times, they had him
dead to rights, yo. And then, poof.

22:51.200 --> 22:52.315
Dude is like Houdini.

22:52.520 --> 22:54.238
Seriously,
when the going gets tough...

22:54.440 --> 22:56.192
...you don't want a criminal lawyer.

22:56.400 --> 22:59.597
You want a "criminal" lawyer.

22:59.800 --> 23:01.518
Know what I'm saying?

23:03.040 --> 23:05.076
Look, we're in good shape,
Mr. White.

23:05.280 --> 23:07.430
Badger is way too loyal to roll.

23:07.640 --> 23:09.517
Plus, he's scared shitless of me,
all right.

23:09.720 --> 23:13.838
We pay four large. Cost of business.
Take it out of his payroll.

23:14.040 --> 23:15.712
And it's only his first dealing rap...

23:15.920 --> 23:18.388
...so, worst-case scenario,
you know, they plead him out.

23:18.600 --> 23:21.990
He does five months picking up litter
in an orange jump suit.

23:23.160 --> 23:26.948
So who goes inside?
I don't need them seeing my face.

23:27.160 --> 23:29.594
Well, I don't need them
seeing my face.

23:29.800 --> 23:32.758
Why not?
You look like his typical clientele.

23:32.960 --> 23:34.359
Dick.

23:34.560 --> 23:35.993
Fine.

23:36.560 --> 23:39.074
We'll flip for it, all right? Call it.

23:40.600 --> 23:42.158
Heads.

23:54.480 --> 23:57.677
Mayhew? Mr. Mayhew?

24:10.600 --> 24:12.875
Mr. Mayhew.

24:13.080 --> 24:15.913
Nice of you to come down. Please.

24:16.240 --> 24:17.309
Look at you.

24:17.720 --> 24:21.349
Should I call the FBl
and tell them I found D.B. Cooper?

24:21.720 --> 24:22.675
Joking.

24:22.880 --> 24:24.871
I-- Please, come on.

24:25.080 --> 24:26.798
Come on. Please.

24:27.000 --> 24:28.718
Hello.

24:29.120 --> 24:31.953
Saul Goodman. Please sit.

24:34.480 --> 24:39.110
So it's a shame that we have to meet
under these circumstances.

24:43.320 --> 24:46.153
I believe you have
something for me?

24:46.480 --> 24:48.391
Oh, yes.

24:50.920 --> 24:55.072
-Mayhew. Is that lrish or English?
-lrish.

24:55.280 --> 24:57.999
Faith and begorra.
A fellow potato-eater.

24:59.160 --> 25:00.479
My real name is McGill.

25:01.080 --> 25:02.798
The Jew thing
I just do for the homeboys.

25:03.000 --> 25:06.879
They all want a pipe-hitting member
of the tribe, so to speak.

25:07.440 --> 25:10.193
I digress.
Good things are happening.

25:10.400 --> 25:14.075
Fact is, your nephew is gonna
get out in no time.

25:14.280 --> 25:15.838
That's wonderful, yeah.

25:16.040 --> 25:18.315
There's still a few details
to be ironed out...

25:18.520 --> 25:20.397
...but now that the DEA
is involved...

25:20.840 --> 25:24.150
...I think he's looking
at time served, then probation.

25:24.360 --> 25:27.591
So leave your number with Francesca,
and we'll be in touch.

25:27.800 --> 25:29.358
-Excuse me, the DEA?
-Yeah.

25:29.560 --> 25:32.996
That's the Drug Enforcement
Administration. The feds.

25:35.640 --> 25:37.995
I hope that I'm not
the breaker of bad news...

25:38.200 --> 25:41.590
...but your nephew got mixed up
with some pretty nasty customers.

25:41.800 --> 25:42.755
I understand that.

25:42.960 --> 25:44.598
What does that have
to do with the DEA?

25:44.800 --> 25:46.233
They're after some mystery man...

25:46.440 --> 25:48.795
...some heavy-hitter
that goes by the name Heisenberg.

25:49.000 --> 25:51.309
They want this guy
like the axe wants the turkey.

25:51.520 --> 25:53.351
Seems young Brandon
may have information...

25:53.560 --> 25:55.312
...that could lead to his arrest.

25:55.840 --> 25:57.751
Jesus, cheer up.
This is good news.

25:57.960 --> 26:00.394
I mean, Brandon fell head-first
into the doo-doo pile...

26:00.600 --> 26:02.477
...and came up
smelling like Paco Rabanne.

26:03.560 --> 26:06.632
Wait, wait. Look, I just.... I think....

26:06.840 --> 26:11.755
I just think that we should
review our options.

26:11.960 --> 26:13.313
Options?

26:13.520 --> 26:15.431
I'm gonna tell you
what your options are.

26:15.640 --> 26:19.076
You got a grand total of two.
Option A: Brandon takes the deal.

26:19.280 --> 26:21.350
Option B:
Brandon goes up to the penitentiary...

26:21.560 --> 26:24.074
...and gets his rectum
resized about yay big.

26:24.280 --> 26:27.750
Look, look. What about reprisals?

26:27.960 --> 26:29.678
I mean, if Badger--

26:29.880 --> 26:35.113
If Brandon informs
on this Heisenberg....

26:35.600 --> 26:37.192
I mean, what if, God forbid...

26:37.400 --> 26:41.996
...that they decide to take revenge?

26:42.200 --> 26:43.918
What have you been telling him?

26:44.120 --> 26:47.396
The kid keeps spouting off about,
"lf I talk, they'll kill me."

26:47.600 --> 26:50.398
Right now, he's the only thing
holding up this deal.

26:51.320 --> 26:54.118
-Good.
-No, that's not good. That's terrible.

26:54.320 --> 26:57.278
Trust me, sir, your nephew
won't last in prison two weeks.

26:57.480 --> 27:00.040
You let him take his chances
on the outside.

27:00.240 --> 27:02.117
Maybe I can work
in some witness protection.

27:02.320 --> 27:05.835
No, look, look.
These are vicious, desperate people.

27:06.040 --> 27:10.795
I've been told that
one of them killed another man...

27:11.000 --> 27:14.310
...by crushing his head
with an ATM machine.

27:15.480 --> 27:17.835
People love to take credit
for the fun ones.

27:18.040 --> 27:21.350
The guy who got his head smooshed
used to be a client of mine.

27:21.560 --> 27:24.028
His wife killed him, all right?
It was open and shut.

27:24.240 --> 27:26.629
Trust me, you folks have
nothing to worry about, okay?

27:26.840 --> 27:30.037
I'm gonna set your nephew straight,
get him singing like a canary...

27:30.240 --> 27:32.549
...all's right with the world.

27:34.560 --> 27:36.596
Ten thousand dollars.

27:49.720 --> 27:52.393
Ten thousand, cash to you.

27:53.560 --> 27:57.075
I'm not saying to throw the case.

27:57.280 --> 28:02.149
Just no talking to the DEA.

28:03.160 --> 28:05.355
Are you saying
what I think you're saying?

28:06.120 --> 28:07.439
Yes.

28:08.280 --> 28:09.998
What's it going to be?

28:12.400 --> 28:14.630
What, dude wouldn't take a bribe?

28:15.040 --> 28:17.679
That dude in there?
Saul Goodman we're talking about?

28:17.880 --> 28:19.472
Yeah. "Morally outraged," he said.

28:19.680 --> 28:21.033
Threatened to call the police.

28:21.240 --> 28:25.995
-Wait, and Badger is gonna spill?
-Like the Exxon Valdez.

28:27.000 --> 28:28.991
So, what do we do about it?

28:39.240 --> 28:41.196
Hey, Francesca,
how about I follow you home?

28:41.400 --> 28:42.389
No.

28:42.600 --> 28:44.192
For safety.

28:44.400 --> 28:45.879
What?

28:47.600 --> 28:50.433
God, you are killing me
with that booty.

29:02.600 --> 29:05.034
Talk to me.
Come on, talk to me, guys, huh?

29:05.240 --> 29:08.710
Come on, just tell me what you want.
Jesus!

29:09.920 --> 29:11.911
Oh, no, no, no!

29:12.120 --> 29:14.918
No, it wasn't me.
It was lgnacio. He's the one.

29:15.120 --> 29:17.759
Oh, no. Oh, no, no, no.

29:20.520 --> 29:22.317
Shut up, dude.

29:22.760 --> 29:25.752
Shut up, all right?
Just speak English.

29:25.960 --> 29:28.713
Lalo didn't send you? No Lalo?

29:29.240 --> 29:32.312
-Who?
-Oh, thank God! Oh, Christ!

29:32.520 --> 29:34.954
Oh, I thought....

29:35.920 --> 29:37.990
What can I do for you gentlemen?

29:38.200 --> 29:40.509
Anything.
Just tell me what you need.

29:40.720 --> 29:44.633
This afternoon, an associate of ours
offered you $10,000.

29:44.840 --> 29:46.319
You should have taken it.

29:46.520 --> 29:49.478
Wait a minute.
This is in regards to what's-his-name?

29:49.680 --> 29:51.989
Badger! Brandon Mayhew.

29:52.360 --> 29:54.590
The uncle. That was your guy?

29:55.760 --> 29:58.399
No offence, but I don't take bribes
from strangers, you know?

29:58.600 --> 30:00.830
Better safe than sorry.
That's my motto.

30:01.040 --> 30:05.272
-But I'll take your money! Sure!
-No, that offer has expired, yo.

30:05.480 --> 30:09.234
It was kind of low anyways.
But okay, okay, I'll take it.

30:09.440 --> 30:11.078
Just tell me what you need,
all right?

30:11.280 --> 30:13.271
I'm easy. I'm gonna keep
a happy thought...

30:13.480 --> 30:15.675
...and assume
this is just a negotiating tactic.

30:15.880 --> 30:18.792
All right, listen to me very carefully.

30:19.000 --> 30:20.797
You are going to give
Badger Mayhew...

30:21.000 --> 30:23.992
...the best legal representation ever.

30:24.200 --> 30:26.350
But no deals with the DEA.

30:26.560 --> 30:30.075
All right? Badger will not identify
anyone to anybody.

30:30.280 --> 30:32.714
If he does, you're dead.

30:34.680 --> 30:36.955
Why don't you just kill Badger?

30:39.840 --> 30:42.513
I mean, follow me, but if a mosquito
is buzzing around you...

30:42.720 --> 30:45.792
...and it bites you on the ass,
you don't go gunning for the attorney.

30:46.000 --> 30:49.276
You go grab a fly swatter.
I mean, so to speak.

30:49.680 --> 30:52.717
I mean, all due respect,
but do I have to spell this out for you?

30:53.280 --> 30:56.192
-We're not killing Badger, yo!
-Then you got real problems, okay.

30:56.400 --> 30:58.311
Because the DEA
will come down on your boy...

30:58.520 --> 31:00.351
...Iike a proverbial ton of bricks.

31:00.560 --> 31:02.551
I don't think
I'm going out on a limb here...

31:02.760 --> 31:04.478
...but, hey,
he's not gonna like prison.

31:04.680 --> 31:08.992
He's gonna sing like Celine Dion
regardless of what you do to me.

31:14.360 --> 31:15.588
Mr. Mayhew?

31:18.200 --> 31:21.670
I recognise your cough. Take that
mask off, you know. Get some air.

31:22.040 --> 31:23.473
Go on.

31:30.360 --> 31:31.918
-God.
-Take it easy.

31:32.120 --> 31:34.634
Breathe in, breathe out.

31:34.840 --> 31:38.549
All right. I'm gonna stand up, all right?
Because I got bad knees.

31:39.280 --> 31:41.032
That's better.

31:41.760 --> 31:45.196
Okay, now listen. The three of us
are gonna work this out.

31:45.400 --> 31:46.833
Yeah? How?

31:47.080 --> 31:49.674
First thing, you'll put a dollar
in my pocket, both of you.

31:52.400 --> 31:54.470
You want attorney-client privilege,
don't you?

31:54.680 --> 31:57.592
So that everything you say
is strictly between us.

31:58.800 --> 32:00.552
I mean it. Put a dollar in my pocket.

32:00.760 --> 32:02.318
Come on, make it official.

32:03.280 --> 32:04.952
Come on, do it.

32:06.160 --> 32:08.833
That's it, come on. Just a dollar.

32:12.880 --> 32:16.395
All right, now you, ski bum.
Come on. Give with the dollar.

32:17.040 --> 32:18.029
-Go on.
-Be smart.

32:18.240 --> 32:19.639
What?

32:23.160 --> 32:24.878
-All I got is a five.
-I'll take a five.

32:25.080 --> 32:28.516
Come on, already.
Come on. Be cool.

32:30.760 --> 32:32.751
Okay, you're now both
officially represented...

32:32.960 --> 32:34.473
...by Saul Goodman and Associates.

32:34.680 --> 32:38.878
Your secrets are safe with me
under threat of disbarment. All right?

32:39.280 --> 32:42.431
Take the ski mask off. I feel like I'm
talking to the Weather Underground.

32:44.280 --> 32:46.157
Just do it.

32:50.600 --> 32:53.831
Okay, so if a prison shanking
is completely off the table....

32:54.040 --> 32:55.234
And we're sure of that?

32:57.760 --> 32:59.193
No shanking!

33:01.120 --> 33:02.553
All right, all right.

33:03.160 --> 33:07.392
The way I see it is
somebody is going to prison.

33:11.160 --> 33:12.957
It's just a matter of who.

33:14.360 --> 33:17.477
All right. Lame-ass TV ads aside...

33:17.680 --> 33:21.036
...your lawyer here,
he cooked you up a pretty killer deal.

33:21.240 --> 33:22.434
Time served, no probation.

33:22.640 --> 33:25.837
It's pretty slick.
Couldn't believe the judge went for it.

33:26.720 --> 33:28.995
Don't get cocky.
You ain't home free yet.

33:29.200 --> 33:31.156
You don't give us
the name of your supplier...

33:31.360 --> 33:34.432
-...you're going nowhere.
-The tough guy act is unnecessary.

33:34.640 --> 33:36.835
This young man
is cooperating fully.

33:37.040 --> 33:39.838
Is that right?
Yeah, you cooperating?

33:43.640 --> 33:46.393
Okay, let's start with a name.

33:48.760 --> 33:50.751
He just goes by Heisenberg.

33:51.280 --> 33:52.235
Heisenberg, huh?

33:53.560 --> 33:54.959
How old is this Heisenberg?

33:55.640 --> 33:59.269
Old. Like 50 or 70 or something.

33:59.480 --> 34:01.516
-Height?
-Average, I guess.

34:01.720 --> 34:03.517
Medium height, medium weight.

34:03.720 --> 34:06.598
-What colour hair?
-No hair.

34:06.800 --> 34:08.358
Dude is balder than you.

34:10.480 --> 34:12.835
1963, James Edward Kilkelly...

34:13.040 --> 34:15.429
...is convicted of stealing
a vending machine.

34:15.639 --> 34:18.313
1975, breaking and entering.

34:18.520 --> 34:21.034
1982, grand theft auto.

34:21.239 --> 34:23.469
1984, armed robbery.

34:23.679 --> 34:27.831
1987, 1992. You get the idea.
And here he is today.

34:28.040 --> 34:29.837
Better known as Jimmy ln-'N-Out.

34:30.040 --> 34:35.319
City, state and federal, he's spent
44 of the last 58 years inside.

34:36.280 --> 34:38.635
Entire life behind bars.

34:39.120 --> 34:41.270
Jimmy provides
a very special service.

34:41.480 --> 34:44.199
For a price,
Jimmy will go to prison for you.

34:45.159 --> 34:48.708
On purpose?
The guy goes to prison on purpose?

34:49.600 --> 34:51.431
He's actually
more comfortable inside.

34:51.639 --> 34:53.949
The outside world
hasn't been too kind to him.

34:55.920 --> 34:57.831
Sometime during
the Clinton administration...

34:58.040 --> 35:01.999
...Jimmy figured out how he could
use his talents to turn a profit.

35:06.320 --> 35:10.916
-So when does all this happen?
-It's already happening.

35:11.120 --> 35:12.348
The buy is set for tomorrow.

35:12.560 --> 35:15.120
Cops bust Jimmy, Badger gets out,
everybody's happy...

35:15.320 --> 35:18.198
...and all it's gonna cost you
is 80 thousand and one pound...

35:18.400 --> 35:19.833
...of your finest meth.

35:24.280 --> 35:27.955
Eighty thousand dollars
for eight years of his life, huh?

35:28.160 --> 35:30.276
First of all,
he's not gonna do eight years.

35:30.480 --> 35:32.198
I'll represent him, and I guarantee...

35:32.400 --> 35:35.756
...there's gonna be some unexpected
problems with the prosecution's case.

35:35.960 --> 35:38.474
Secondly, he gets 30.
Fifty goes to me.

35:38.680 --> 35:41.592
-You get 50? For what?
-For facilitating.

35:41.800 --> 35:44.360
Who's taking a bigger risk here?
He likes prison.

35:44.560 --> 35:46.471
You did bring the cash, didn't you?

35:46.680 --> 35:49.638
Look, if this option
is too expensive...

35:49.840 --> 35:53.116
...you can still always...Badger
in the chow line.

36:10.680 --> 36:12.671
Conscience gets expensive,
doesn't it?

36:29.400 --> 36:31.789
All right. There's our boy.

36:32.920 --> 36:35.115
Right on time.

36:51.120 --> 36:53.998
-Go back.
-What? All right, all right, all right.

37:06.360 --> 37:09.830
So, what do you think?
They see us?

37:10.240 --> 37:12.037
No, man, I think we're good.

37:17.240 --> 37:19.231
Badger looks like
he's gonna throw up.

37:19.640 --> 37:21.039
Give me those back.

37:21.240 --> 37:23.117
Just give them to me.

37:23.760 --> 37:25.478
Oh, no.

37:26.040 --> 37:27.189
Where the hell is Jimmy?

37:27.400 --> 37:29.311
Should've been here
10 minutes ago.

37:29.520 --> 37:34.036
You think Jimmy is actually for real?
A guy who wants to be in prison?

37:34.600 --> 37:36.511
There's more
than one kind of prison.

37:36.720 --> 37:38.472
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

37:38.680 --> 37:41.035
There he is-- Wait a minute.

37:41.240 --> 37:44.630
-Oh, no, no, no.
-What? What? Let me see.

37:46.120 --> 37:48.236
-Who the hell is that?
-I don't know.

37:51.800 --> 37:54.633
Mr. Heisenberg, I presume.

37:55.640 --> 37:57.232
Time to move?

37:57.520 --> 37:59.476
Not till we see the exchange.

38:02.200 --> 38:05.078
No, no. Oh, shit!

38:05.280 --> 38:08.238
-What?
-Now he shows.

38:11.600 --> 38:13.431
Okay, let's do this.

38:17.440 --> 38:18.714
No, no.

38:18.920 --> 38:21.354
Oh, my God.
Jimmy is on the wrong bench. Crap!

38:21.560 --> 38:23.551
We're screwed!

38:23.760 --> 38:25.079
What are you doing?

38:25.280 --> 38:27.316
Hey, what are you doing?

38:31.240 --> 38:33.037
I don't get it. What's the holdup?

38:43.320 --> 38:44.548
Where's the stuff, man?

38:44.760 --> 38:46.796
-Where are we going?
-Just shut up.

38:52.440 --> 38:53.589
Get out. Go stop him.

38:53.800 --> 38:56.109
The DEA is right there.
If they see me, we're screwed.

38:56.320 --> 38:57.753
Get out. I'll do something.

38:57.960 --> 38:59.871
-What?
-Just go!

39:12.280 --> 39:14.316
Hank, I thought that was you.

39:14.520 --> 39:16.033
Schrader, I'm blocked.

39:16.240 --> 39:18.879
-Walt, not a good time.
-How you doing? You feeling okay?

39:19.080 --> 39:20.035
Schrader, I'm blocked.

39:20.720 --> 39:22.631
We're working.
You gotta get out of here.

39:22.840 --> 39:26.037
-Working? Oh, like DEA working?
-Schrader, we're missing it. Schrader.

39:26.240 --> 39:28.196
Is something going down?

39:30.360 --> 39:32.794
Wrong guy, wrong guy.
Other bench.

39:39.320 --> 39:40.389
Walt, Walt.

39:40.600 --> 39:42.636
-Walter, move your ass now.
-Okay.

39:42.840 --> 39:44.558
Listen, I'll just go, leave you alone.

39:44.760 --> 39:47.433
-We'll talk about it later. Just floor it.
-Should I back up?

39:47.640 --> 39:48.993
-Go that way.
-Forward is better?

39:49.200 --> 39:50.952
I'll be out of the way there.
Okay, okay.

39:51.160 --> 39:53.515
I'm sorry, all right? I'm sorry.

39:53.720 --> 39:56.188
-I'll leave you alone.
-We'll talk later. Just go.

39:56.920 --> 39:59.673
Where'd he go?
Where the hell did he go?

40:01.560 --> 40:04.677
Oh, wait. Wait, wait, wait. Got him.

40:11.640 --> 40:13.915
-Looks like it's going down.
-Take him.

40:21.600 --> 40:24.478
Freeze! Hey, right there.
Don't move.

40:26.800 --> 40:28.153
Come on, let's get him up.

40:37.560 --> 40:39.152
Jesus!

40:40.120 --> 40:41.872
I think they bought it.

40:45.480 --> 40:46.469
Absolutely.

40:46.680 --> 40:49.911
Textbook bust, sir. Yes, sir.

40:50.120 --> 40:52.554
Looks like we got a full pound
of the blue stuff.

40:52.760 --> 40:57.311
Oh, and Heisenberg's real name?
James Kilkelly.

40:58.560 --> 41:02.473
Thank you. Thank you very much.
It was my pleasure.

41:28.120 --> 41:29.394
Hey.

41:30.360 --> 41:32.749
You weren't home,
so I let the delivery guys in.

41:32.960 --> 41:36.236
-I hope that's okay.
-Absolutely.

41:45.240 --> 41:47.310
So you bought a bed.

41:48.720 --> 41:49.789
Yeah.

41:50.360 --> 41:51.998
What is that, a king?

41:54.400 --> 41:55.913
Pillow top?

42:30.640 --> 42:34.394
Oh, my God.
You really are a chemistry teacher.

42:39.160 --> 42:40.593
You mind?

42:44.520 --> 42:46.636
I was terrible at chemistry.

42:46.840 --> 42:49.354
I'm more of a humanities guy.

42:49.560 --> 42:52.028
-How did you find me?
-We should talk about that.

42:52.240 --> 42:56.392
It should be much, much harder
for people to track you down.

42:56.600 --> 42:58.158
My Pl charged me for three hours...

42:58.360 --> 43:01.193
...so I seriously doubt
it took him more than one.

43:04.000 --> 43:06.992
So this is, what, blackmail?

43:07.200 --> 43:08.838
Walter, I'm your lawyer.

43:09.040 --> 43:13.272
Anything you say to me
is totally privileged.

43:13.480 --> 43:15.914
I'm not in the shakedown racket.

43:16.120 --> 43:18.429
I'm a lawyer. Even drug dealers
need lawyers, right?

43:18.640 --> 43:21.632
Especially drug dealers.

43:22.040 --> 43:25.919
So, what, you're just doing this
out of the kindness of your heart?

43:26.440 --> 43:29.591
Come on.
Have you seen my hourly rate?

43:30.840 --> 43:32.717
By the way,
where do you keep the money?

43:32.920 --> 43:37.038
Is it in your mattress? Is it in a jelly jar
buried in the side yard?

43:37.240 --> 43:40.073
This kid Mayhew may be the first
of your guys to get picked up...

43:40.280 --> 43:41.508
...but he won't be the last.

43:41.720 --> 43:45.110
And if I can find you,
how far behind can the cops be?

43:45.320 --> 43:46.673
I don't understand.

43:46.880 --> 43:49.633
What exactly are you
offering to do for me?

43:51.080 --> 43:53.992
What did Tom Hagen
do for Vito Corleone?

43:54.400 --> 43:57.358
I'm no Vito Corleone.

43:57.560 --> 44:00.199
No shit. Right now, you're Fredo.

44:00.400 --> 44:01.833
But with some sound advice...

44:02.040 --> 44:04.315
...and the proper introductions,
who knows?

44:04.520 --> 44:06.397
I'll tell you,
you've got the right product.

44:06.600 --> 44:09.239
Anything that gets the DEA's panties
in this big a bunch...

44:09.440 --> 44:11.032
...you're on to something special.

44:11.240 --> 44:15.438
And I would like to be
a small and silent part of it.

44:17.920 --> 44:18.909
Food for thought, yeah?

44:23.920 --> 44:28.391
So if you wanna make more money
and keep the money that you make...

44:29.640 --> 44:31.596
...better call Saul!

